{{Infobox company | name = Glow Energy PCL | logo = Glow Energy Logo.jpg | caption = | type = [[Public company|Public]] | traded_as = {{SET|GLOW}} | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = {{start date|1993|10}} <ref name=GLOW2009AR>{{cite book|title=Annual Report 2009|year=2010|url=http://glow.listedcompany.com/misc/ar/ar2009_part02.pdf|author=Glow Energy|authorlink=Glow Energy|accessdate=18 November 2011}}</ref> | founder = | defunct = | location_city = [[Bangkok]] | location_country = [[Thailand]] | locations = | area_served = Thailand, [[Laos]] | key_people = Brendan Wauters ([[CEO]]) | industry = [[Electricity]] | products = | services = | revenue = 65,369 million baht (2015) | operating_income = 64,225 million baht (2015) | net_income = 8,355 million baht (2015) | assets = 117,169 million baht (2015) | equity = 55,958 million baht (20150 | owner = | num_employees = 800+ (2015) | parent = [[Engie]] | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|http://www.glow.co.th/}} | footnotes = | intl = }} '''Glow Energy PCL''' is a power and utility company in [[Thailand]] established in 1993. Glow Energy is one of the largest private [[electricity]] generators in [[Thailand]].<ref name=hoovers>{{cite web | url = http://www.hoovers.com/glow-energy/--ID__139529--/free-co-profile.xhtml | title= Glow Energy Company Description | publisher = Hoover's, Inc. | accessdate=2009-01-22}}</ref> Its core business is to produce and supply electricity to [[EGAT]], and to produce and deliver electricity, steam, and processed water to industrial customers. EGAT power purchase agreements are central to Glow's business, accounting for 59.7 percent of revenues in 2015.<ref name="AR-2015" />{{RP|55}} Glow Energy is a [[subsidiary]] of [[Engie]]. The French energy company has a 69.11 percent stake in Glow.<ref name="AR-2015" />{{RP|67}}
The company has four major production facilities in industrial areas in [[Rayong Province|Rayong]] and [[Chonburi Province]]s. {{As of|2015|12|31}}, the company had a total generating capacity of 3,207&nbsp;MW of electricity and 1,206&nbsp;tons per hour of steam. Electricity sales accounted for over 85.4 percent of total revenues in 2015. The sale of steam accounted for 12.1 percent. In addition to Thailand, Glow Energy operates a hydroelectric plant in [[Lao PDR]]'s [[Attapeu Province]].<ref name="AR-2015">{{cite book|title=Annual Report, 2015|date=2016|publisher=Glow Energy Public Company Limited|location=Bangkok|url=http://glow.listedcompany.com/misc/ar/20160404-glow-ar2015-en-02.pdf|accessdate=5 October 2016}}</ref>{{RP|68}}<ref name=forbes>{{cite news |url= https://www.forbes.com/afxnewslimited/feeds/afx/2008/09/15/afx5422654.html |title=Thai Glow buys Laos power plant for $45 mln |publisher=[[Forbes]] |date=2008-09-15 |accessdate=2009-01-22}}{{Dead link|date=October 2016}}</ref><ref name=reuters100908>{{cite news | agency=Reuters | title= Thai Glow Energy close to power plant deal in Laos | url= https://www.reuters.com/article/rbssIndustryMaterialsUtilitiesNews/idUSBKK6597720080910 | date = 2008-09-10 | accessdate=2009-01-22}}</ref>
Glow generates electricity using natural gas (62.6 percent of total cost of sales in 2015), coal (16.8 percent of total cost of sales in 2015), and, increasingly, solar.<ref name="AR-2015" />{{RP|59}}
==Financials== Glow in 2015 reported revenues of 65,369 million [[Thai baht|baht]], total assets of 117,169 million baht, and a net profit of 8,355 million baht, all down from [[fiscal year|FY2014]] results.<ref name="AR-2015" />{{RP|12}} The company employed over 800 persons.<ref name="AR-2015" />
