{{Infobox power station | name = Jiaxing Power Station | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = | location_map_size = | location_map_caption= | coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | country = China | location = [[Jiaxing]], [[Zhejiang]] | status = O | construction_began = 1995 | commissioned = 1995-2011 | decommissioned = | cost = US$15.78&nbsp;billion | owner = Zhejiang Energy Group Co Ltd | operator = [[Zhejiang Jiaxing Power Generation Co Ltd]] | th_fuel_primary = [[Bituminous coal]] | th_fuel_tertiary = | ps_thermal_capacity = | ps_units_operational= 2 X 300&nbsp;MW 4 X 600&nbsp;MW 2 X 1000&nbsp;MW | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_cancelled = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | ps_electrical_capacity= 5000 [[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_electrical_cap_fac= | website = | extra = }}
The '''Jiaxing Power Station''' is a state-owned 5000 megawatt [[coal fired power station]] owned by Zhejiang Energy Group Co Ltd in [[Zhejiang]]. The $15.78 billion plant is situated in [[Jiaxing]].
The plant consists of two 300MW sub-critical units, four 600MW super-critical units and two 1000MW ultra-supercritical units, which combined form the 5000MW plant.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zhejiang Jiaxing Coal Power Plant China|url=http://globalenergyobservatory.org/geoid/41940|publisher=Global Energy Observatory|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
