{{Forestry-stub}}
{{tree-stub}}

'''Máire Mullarney''' (1 September 1921 – 18 August 2008<ref>http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/ireland/2008/0819/1218868120714.html</ref>) was an [[Ireland|Irish]] environmentalist, educationalist and [[Esperanto]] advocate. She was one of the founding members of the [[Green Party (Ireland)|Irish Green Party]] in 1981. She stood for the party in three [[Dáil Éireann|Dáil]] elections in the 1980s and was elected to Dublin County Council in 1991, a position she kept until 1999.

Maire Mullarney also published a book called "Anything school can do you can do better" it was about her raising her children as well as home educating.

